textBeforeTable: Top 5 wettest May's and calendar year's on record in San Juan, PR     May 2010 was the 4th wettest May on record and the 12th consecutive month at the Luis Muñoz Marin International Airport in San Juan where the average temperature was above normal. A list of the top 5 wettest Mays and last 12 months of temperatures at the Luis Muñoz Marin International Airport in San Juan can be found in the tables below. In addition, the total accumulated precipitation of 31.21" through the end of May represents the wettest start to a year on record, 1.45" above the same date in 2005, the previous wettest year through the month of May. (Records from the Luis Muñoz Marin International Airport date back to January 1, 1956).   Questions?
